T1  - The analysis of risky investment: A State-Contingent Approach
AU  - Kroll, Yoram
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 8
IS  - 4
SP  - 509
EP  - 524
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/12/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/S0378-4266(84)80043-6
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0378426684800436
AB  - The paper extends the stochastic dominance analysis into a state-contingent framework. Unlike the regular stochastic dominance rules in which case the dominance is defined over the states, the efficiency analysis is applicable also for prospects that can be diversified between themselves or with other assets. The paper presents definitions of the state-contingent dominance rules, theorems with respect to the properties of these rules, comparisons between the regular stochastic dominance rules, the state-contingent dominance rules, and demonstrations of some economic implications and uses of these rules.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - A case study on the effectiveness of foreign exchange market intervention: The Italian Lira (September 1975–March 1977)
AU  - Micossi, S.
AU  - Rebecchini, S.
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 8
IS  - 4
SP  - 535
EP  - 555
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/12/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/S0378-4266(84)80045-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S037842668480045X
AB  - This paper discusses Italy's policies of official intervention on foreign exchange markets and their rôle in restoring orderly conditions after the foreign exchange crisis of February 1976. For these purposes, daily time series of official intervention, the exchange rate and interest rates have been collected and analyzed with standard statistical methods as well as with vector autoregression techniques. The results seem to show that intervention had some effect in moderating exchange rate variability and perhaps in avoiding an unwarranted depreciation of the lira and lend some support to the contention that intervention can increase the authorities' room for maneuver.
ER  - 

